- "digital garden" refers to the social media platform where users post tweets;
- "richness of their interactions" refers to the engagement rate of the tweets;
- "average engagement rate" is calculated as the average of the engagement rates of all tweets posted by a user.

- 'Marketing staff' refers to users with the role 'marketing staff' in the user table;
- 'Marketing and Communications' refers to a department in the company;
- 'Sentiment' is categorized as 'Positive', 'Negative', or 'Neutral' based on the sentiment score;
- 'Average engagement rate' is calculated by averaging the engagement rates for each tweet.

